lr
------------------------------------------
lr is a new tool for generating file listings, which includes the best features
of ls(1), find(1), stat(1) and du(1).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/leahneukirchen/lr

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/leahneukirchen/lr/archive/v1.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack lr-1.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./lr-1.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/lr-1.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/lr-1.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(lr)
  /usr/bin/lr.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/lr.README
  /usr/share/doc/lr/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/lr/NEWS.md
  /usr/share/doc/lr/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/lr.1.gz
  /usr/share/zsh/site-functions/_lr

------------------

